CODE: 
# Accept input from the user 
input_str = input("Enter a comma-separated sequence of words: ") 
 
# Split the input by commas, remove duplicates, and sort alphabetically 
words = sorted(set(input_str.split(','))) 
 
# Convert the sorted words back to a string 
result_str = ', '.join(words) 
 
# Print the distinct words in sorted form 
print("Distinct words in sorted form:", result_str) 
 
 
OUTPUT: 
Enter a comma-separated sequence of words: red, white, black, red, 
green, black 
Distinct words in sorted form:  black,  green,  red,  white
